Sun Hints at a PowerPC Solaris Port	A <a href="http://blogs.sun.com/roller/page/jonathan/20040808#rewriting_history_and_vocabulary" target="_blank">blog entry</a> from Sun's second in command, Jonathan Schwartz, is indicating that a demo of Solaris capable of running on IBM's PowerPC architecture is on its way. When asked for comment a Sun spokesperson told BetaNews, "We don't have anything more to say about it at this point beyond what is in Jonathan's blog." More <a href="http://www.betanews.com/article/1077577572" target="_blank">detailed information</a> on Solaris 10 is available from BetaNews.
